sentences: Hanin Elias (born 31 May 1972) is a Syrian German industrial/techno artist.

After Atari Teenage Riot's non-definitive break in 2000, and the subsequent death of Carl Crack from a drug overdose, the members of ATR split up, and Elias set up her own record label, Fatal Recordings.
In 2005, Elias began working with the industrial project Pigface, joining them on their US tour.
In 2006, it was announced that Fatal Recordings was to close.
In 2010, Hanin moved back to Berlin/Germany in order to prepare a new album for 2011.

In June 2011, the new album Get It Back on Rustblade Recordings was released.
In February 2014, Hanin Elias released an album under the name of 'Fantome', with her co-musician Marcel Zürcher who plays guitar and writes songs for Die Krupps.
In 2016, her collaboration with the French producer Electrosexual marks the release of the single Hold Me  and "Automatic People" (Rock Machine Records)
She was a member of Atari Teenage Riot and is now a solo artist.
Elias was born in Wittlich, Rhineland-Palatinate, Germany and spent three years of her early life living in Syria.
